South African Transport Unions to Report to Striking Members on New Offer

-- B y   L a u r e n   v a n   d e r   W e s t h u i z e n
-- 
2011-02-18T06:25:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-18/south-african-transport-unions-to-report-to-striking-members-on-new-offer.html
South African labor unions leading a
strike by the nation’s freight workers will report back to their
members today with the latest offer from employers, Gabudi
Ramakgolo, a coordinator for the South African Transport and
Allied Workers’ Union, said.  Talks will resume at 2 p.m. South African time, he said in
a telephone interview. The strike is in its fifth day.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lauren van der Westhuizen in  Cape Town  at 
 lvanderwesth@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vernon Wessels at 
 vwessels@bloomberg.net  